Item.Name: Standing crop

Item.Name: Stacked/baled crop (incl manure heap)
Item.ScopeNotes: Recently cropped arable, horticultural land with crops stacked in bales, etc.

Item.Name: Woodland/forest - conifers/softwood
Item.ScopeNotes: Woodland - defined as more than 20% of an area covered in tree canopies (branches). Mature conifer trees in plantation or wood consisting of species that includes; pines, firs, spruces, larch and other conifers species (excluding yew). Includes trees in copses, shelterbelts and groups of trees in rural parklands and arboretums.

Item.Name: Woodland/forest - broadleaf/hardwood
Item.ScopeNotes: Woodland - defined as more than 20% of an area covered in tree canopies (branches). Mature broadleaved and yew trees, or mixture of broadleaves and conifers, in plantation or wood consisting of species that include: oak, ash, birch, beech, alder, sycamore and other broadleaves species. Includes trees in copses, shelterbelts and groups of trees in rural parklands and arboretums.

Item.Name: Tree scrub (includes single trees not in garden)
Item.ScopeNotes: All other conifer and broadleaved trees including: non-mature trees, single trees, restocked/natural regeneration sites, veteran trees, trees in hedgerows, single trees in rural parkland.

Item.Name: Straw/stubble burning
Item.ScopeNotes: Use for intentional burning by the agricultural community. Cropped arable or horticultural land being burnt off. Any other deliberate ignition should be recorded as 'grassland/pasture/grazing etc'.

Item.Name: Private/Domestic garden/allotment (vegetation not equipment/building)
Item.ScopeNotes: Vegetation not equipment

Item.Name: Nurseries, market garden
Item.ScopeNotes: Smallholding and polytunnel

Item.Name: Heathland or moorland
Item.ScopeNotes: Game shooting heaths/moors, water catchment areas, moors, bogs, peatland formed of dwarf scrub and heath, bogs and bracken.

Item.Name: Grassland, pasture, grazing etc
Item.ScopeNotes: Upland and lowland grassland, horse paddocks, livestock grazing areas, etc.

Item.Name: Scrub land
Item.ScopeNotes: Mixtures of grasslands, heaths, moors, bogs with a high percentage of naturally regenerating trees.

Item.Name: Railway trackside vegetation
Item.ScopeNotes: Vegetation on railway banks, trackside, and surrounding areas. Includes trees and grasses and other species.

Item.Name: Roadside vegetation
Item.ScopeNotes: Vegetation on roadsides, banks, roundabouts and surrounding areas. Includes trees and grasses and other species.

Item.Name: Canal/riverbank vegetation
Item.ScopeNotes: Vegetation on tow paths, banksides and surrounding areas. Includes trees and grasses and other species.

Item.Name: Other outdoor structures
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes Pier (not jetty)

Item.Name: Tunnel, subway
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes Channel Tunnel, Underground/tube system, tunnel not part of railway system

Item.Name: Bridge
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes railway bridge

Item.Name: Railway goods yard
Item.ScopeNotes: Not in building. Includes sidings

Item.Name: Shelter
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes Portable shelter, stand alone smoking shelter, air raid shelter - For bus shelter choose 'Other buildings/use not known'

Item.Name: Other outdoor items including roadside furniture
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes small children's playhouse; playground equipment e.g. slide, decking, stand-alone for sale sign, park bench, freestanding scaffolding, jetty. For other 'outdoor items' without their own specific IRS category, please choose this option.

Item.Name: Outdoor storage
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes gas, oil, petrol, grease, paper, cardboard, timber, rubber, plastic, metal (including storage of scrap metal), coal, coke. Paper packing materials, shavings, sawdust, fallen trees in forest, sheds outside for sale, scrap cars, storage container, silage (including in pit)

Item.Name: Recycling collection point, bottle bank
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes bottle banks

Item.Name: Garden equipment
Item.ScopeNotes: Outdoor storage of garden equipment

Item.Name: Agricultural equipment
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes baling machinery, binder threshing machine, grain dryer, agricultural trailer

Item.Name: Other outdoor equipment/machinery
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes non-agricultural tractor, road making and earth moving equipment, dumper, tar boiler, other mobile equipment e.g. compressor, lawn mower, weather balloon, derrick, cement mixer, fork lift truck, kiln, furnace, incinerator, pylon, switchgear, sub station, generator, transformer, oil pipeline, petrol pump, paraffin dispenser, carwash, fixed crane, vending machine, shoring, welding and cutting equipment, compactor, vehicle used for recreational racing.

Item.Name: Loose refuse (incl in garden)
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes discarded tyres (not recycling)

Item.Name: Park
Item.ScopeNotes: Formal urban parklands that include, within the urban parkland - tree/s, groups of trees, grassland, shrubs, recreational areas, etc.

Item.Name: Wasteland
Item.ScopeNotes: Urban or built up areas of unused land with established or regenerating vegetation

Item.Name: Other outdoor location
Item.ScopeNotes: Includes possessions usually belonging indoors set light to in garden of property.

Item.Name: Mines and quarries - excluding buildings above ground
